3.1 Assert type on unknow type
We use a type assertion (error as Error).message to assert that the error object has the type Error, which guarantees the presence of the message property. This allows TypeScript to recognize and accept the error.message access without any type error.
try {
    const result = await dbManager.runQuery(query);
    res.status(200).json(result.records);
  } catch (error) {
    // res.status(500).json({ error: error.message }); //type error
    res.status(500).json({ error: (error as Error).message });
  }

